# yaml-language-server: $schema=https://coderabbit.ai/integrations/schema.v2.json
# https://docs.coderabbit.ai/reference/configuration

language: "uk-UA"

tone_instructions: >
  Be direct and constructive. Focus on architecture violations, business logic correctness,
  and security issues. Avoid nitpicking formatting that ESLint/Prettier already handles.

early_access: false

reviews:
  profile: "assertive"
  request_changes_workflow: false
  high_level_summary: true
  high_level_summary_instructions: >
    Summarize the PR in 3-5 bullet points. Mention which FSD layer or DDD sub-layer was changed
    (common / client / server / app), and whether online/offline parity was maintained.
  poem: false
  review_status: true
  collapse_walkthrough: false
  sequence_diagrams: true

  auto_review:
    enabled: true
    drafts: false
    base_branches:
      - "main"

  path_filters:
    - "!**/*.lock"
    - "!**/package-lock.json"
    - "!**/yarn.lock"
    - "!**/pnpm-lock.yaml"
    - "!**/.next/**"
    - "!**/dist/**"
    - "!**/build/**"
    - "!**/*.snap"
    - "!**/migrations/*.ts"   # migrations are generated â€” review separately if needed
    - "!**/seeders/**"

  # â”€â”€â”€ Global review instructions â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€
  instructions: |
    This is FinMan â€” a Next.js 15 full-stack financial manager with strict layered architecture.
    Read the rules below before reviewing any file.

    ## Layer Boundaries (HARD rules â€” always flag violations)
    - `src/common/` must NEVER import from `src/client/` or `src/server/`.
    - `src/client/` must NEVER import from `src/server/` (and vice versa).
    - `src/app/` pages must contain NO business logic â€” they are routing shells only.
    - FSD import hierarchy (top â†’ bottom only): app â†’ widgets â†’ features â†’ entities â†’ shared/database
      Flag any import that goes upward (e.g. `shared` importing from `features`).

    ## Online/Offline Parity
    - Every entity that touches data must have BOTH a `*.local.repository.ts` (IndexedDB/Dexie)
      and a `*.api.client.ts` (HTTP). Flag if only one side is implemented.
    - Features must consume data exclusively through `BasicDataSource` â€” never import a repository
      or api client directly inside a feature, widget, or component.

    ## Repository vs Use Case
    - Repositories must contain ONLY simple atomic CRUD over a single table. Flag any business
      logic or multi-table coordination inside a repository method.
    - Multi-repository operations must live in a `*.use-case.ts` file, never in route `execute`.

    ## API Routes (`createRoute`)
    - Every API route MUST use `createRoute()`. Flag any raw `NextRequest` handler.
    - Security pipeline order: schema validation â†’ contextFn â†’ guards â†’ execute.
    - Authentication check = `AuthGuard`. Existence check = `ExistXxxGuard`. Ownership = `OwnsXxxGuard`.
    - Flag if `execute` contains logic that belongs in a guard (auth/existence/ownership checks).

    ## TypeORM Relations
    - Relations MUST use string references: `@OneToMany('UserOrm', 'country')`.
    - NEVER use the `() => EntityOrm` callback syntax â€” it causes circular imports.

    ## Soft Delete
    - `softDeleted` must be typed `0 | 1`, never `boolean`.

    ## Error Handling
    - All thrown errors must be `AppError` (or subclass) â€” never plain objects or generic `Error`
      from business code.
    - UI components must use `getSafeErrorMessage(error: unknown)` for display â€” never access
      `.message` directly.

    ## Screen State
    - Page-level and list-level state must use `FinListScreenHandler` or `FinFormScreenHandler`.
      Flag any ad-hoc conditional rendering of spinners or error messages in screen components.

    ## Styling
    - NEVER use default Tailwind color utilities (`text-red-500`, `bg-blue-200`, etc.).
      Only semantic token classes (`text-foreground`, `bg-primary`, `text-destructive`, â€¦) are allowed.
    - Variant-dependent colors MUST be defined in SCSS, not inline via Tailwind conditionals.

    ## Naming Conventions
    - Files: kebab-case with required postfix (`.hook.ts`, `.service.ts`, `.repository.ts`,
      `.api.client.ts`, `.use-case.ts`, `.guard.ts`, `.orm.ts`, `.schema.ts`, `.filter.ts`,
      `.record.ts`, `.model.ts`, `.constant.ts`, `.enum.ts`, `.util.ts`, `.props.ts`, `.spec.ts`).
    - React components: PascalCase. Variables/functions: camelCase. CSS classes: kebab-case.
    - `ui-*` prefix = dumb primitive (no business logic). `fin-*` prefix = smart/wired component.

    ## Zod Schemas
    - Validation error messages must be in Ukrainian.
    - Prefer `satisfies` over generic type parameters on schema variables.

    ## Tests
    - Test files: co-located in `__tests__/`, named `*.spec.ts`.
    - Never add `vi.clearAllMocks()` inside individual test files (handled globally).

    ## What NOT to flag
    - Import ordering â€” handled by ESLint.
    - Prettier formatting â€” handled by Prettier.
    - Missing JSDoc on every function â€” not required by this project.
    - TypeORM migration file content â€” migrations are auto-generated.

  # â”€â”€â”€ Path-specific instructions â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€
  path_instructions:
    - path: "src/common/**"
      instructions: |
        This is the Shared Contract Layer. Must be pure TypeScript only.
        Flag any import from `src/client/` or `src/server/`.
        Flag any React hooks, API calls, or DB access.
        Check that records extend `DefaultTableColumns` and use `0 | 1` for softDeleted.
        Zod schema error messages must be in Ukrainian.

    - path: "src/client/database/**"
      instructions: |
        Global IndexedDB infrastructure â€” Dexie wrapper and base CRUD service.
        No business logic allowed here. No entity-specific code.
        Check that `DatabaseLocalService` methods match the `runBatch` / `getItems` API contract.

    - path: "src/client/entities/**"
      instructions: |
        FSD entity slice. Each entity must have both `*.local.repository.ts` and `*.api.client.ts`.
        Local repository must extend `CrudLocalService`. API client must implement `ICrudService`.
        `mapFilters()` override is required if the entity has filter fields.
        No business logic â€” pure CRUD only.

    - path: "src/client/features/**"
      instructions: |
        User scenario layer. Must consume data via `BasicDataSource` service only.
        Flag any direct import of `*.local.repository.ts` or `*.api.client.ts`.
        Hooks must not contain multi-repository coordination â€” extract to use-case if needed.
        Check online/offline parity in the composed service.

    - path: "src/client/shared/components/**"
      instructions: |
        Smart composite components (`fin-*`). May wire UI primitives to RHF, TanStack Query, etc.
        Must NOT contain page-level business logic.
        Check that screen-level state uses FinListScreenHandler / FinFormScreenHandler.

    - path: "src/client/shared/ui/**"
      instructions: |
        Dumb primitive components (`ui-*`). Props and events only â€” no hooks, no business logic,
        no form wiring, no API calls. Completely generic and reusable.
        Variant colors must be in SCSS, not in JSX/Tailwind conditionals.

    - path: "src/server/entities/**"
      instructions: |
        DDD server entity slice. Three sub-layers: domain / application / infrastructure.
        - `*.orm.ts`: TypeORM entity â€” use string references for all relations.
        - `*.repository.ts`: extends `CrudApiRepository` â€” pure CRUD only.
        - Guards: return `null` on pass, `ApiResultOperationError` on fail.
        - Use cases: multi-repo coordination â€” never in route execute.

    - path: "src/app/api/**"
      instructions: |
        API route handlers. MUST use `createRoute()` â€” flag any raw NextRequest handlers.
        Pipeline: schema â†’ contextFn â†’ guards (AuthGuard first) â†’ execute â†’ filter.
        `execute` must contain only business logic, not auth/existence/ownership checks.
        Flag any multi-repo logic directly in `execute` â€” it belongs in a use case.

    - path: "**/__tests__/**"
      instructions: |
        Vitest + Testing Library tests.
        Co-located in `__tests__/`, named `*.spec.ts`.
        No `vi.clearAllMocks()` in test files â€” it's handled globally in vitest config.
        Local repository tests must use in-memory `DatabaseLocalService('UNIT_TESTS', [], 1)`.
        Declare unit vs integration intent at the top of the describe block.

    - path: "src/client/shared/styles/**"
      instructions: |
        Global design tokens and SCSS architecture.
        Changes here affect the entire app â€” review for token naming consistency and
        that new tokens follow the oklch / semantic naming convention already in use.

knowledge_base:
  opt_out: false
  learnings:
    scope: auto
  issues:
    scope: auto
  jira:
    usage: auto
  linear:
    usage: auto
  pull_requests:
    scope: auto

chat:
  auto_reply: true